1
00:00:30,150 --> 00:00:32,080
Here he is, Honey Cheese Pie,

2
00:00:32,110 --> 00:00:34,840
author of "Between Us
and the Deep Forest."

3
00:00:35,010 --> 00:00:37,280
Even after all you did to me.

4
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:39,160
But was any of it ever real?

5
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:43,800
"That sudden surge
through his chest"

6
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:46,800
"was unlike anything
he had ever known."

7
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:50,080
"He traced it back in his mind,"

8
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:54,440
"yet dreaded to feel it again."

9
00:00:55,070 --> 00:00:59,670
"The more he pushed it away,
the more it clung."

10
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:04,800
"Anan's steady hands held Somporn
by the shoulders."

11
00:01:05,250 --> 00:01:08,480
"Somporn trembled in that embrace,"

12
00:01:08,990 --> 00:01:11,800
"as though a war
were being fought within him."

13
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:15,240
"Heat rose to his face,
slow as a gathering flame,"

14
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:19,560
"until Somporn could
no longer remain still."

15
00:01:32,970 --> 00:01:33,970
Here you go.

16
00:01:35,630 --> 00:01:37,800
Who'd you fight with?
Your mom or dad?

17
00:01:41,450 --> 00:01:43,080
Or your grandpa?

18
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:46,440
No, I didn't fight with anyone.

19
00:01:47,620 --> 00:01:48,620
It's just...

20
00:01:50,770 --> 00:01:52,200
something I want to talk through.

21
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:54,560
About?

22
00:01:56,060 --> 00:01:57,060
Uh...

23
00:02:00,460 --> 00:02:02,600
Come on, out with it.

24
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:05,430
You've vented about your parents
to me plenty of times.

25
00:02:05,470 --> 00:02:06,830
Have I judged you once?

26
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,280
It's just...

27
00:02:14,220 --> 00:02:16,040
I kissed a guy.

28
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:20,400
And it felt... good.

29
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:23,240
No, wait. Not exactly good.

30
00:02:24,050 --> 00:02:25,050
I mean...

31
00:02:25,910 --> 00:02:28,560
I'm not sure if it means something.

32
00:02:30,130 --> 00:02:31,440
Can you just give me an answer?

33
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:36,760
Why do you think I'd
have the answer for you?

34
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,280
Why are you asking me?

35
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:40,960
Come on, Uncle Sun. Seriously.

36
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:44,760
Because...you're gay, aren't you?

37
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,120
You knew?

38
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:49,840
Isn't it obvious?

39
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:52,120
It's not exactly a mystery.

40
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:58,680
And...people at home.

41
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,640
Do they know?

42
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:05,000
Hard to say. Probably.
They just don't bring it up.

43
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,160
But hold on.

44
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:10,160
Today's about me, not you.

45
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,930
I don't know who else to go to.

46
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,040
Can you help me figure this out?

47
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,400
Hmm, talk to me.

48
00:03:20,550 --> 00:03:22,950
You remember my friend
I did the live stream with?

49
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:25,240
Guy, right?

50
00:03:25,940 --> 00:03:26,940
Yeah.

51
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,040
You see. He liked me.

52
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:33,360
So I figured
I'd try things out with him.

53
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:36,360
And get some material
for grandpa's BL novel.

54
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,640
Why didn't you just
come to me for material?

55
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:42,440
I didn't want to
make you uncomfortable.

56
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:45,400
Wasn't sure how grandpa
would feel about it either.

57
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,520
So how'd it go?

58
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:51,000
It's just...strange.

59
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,500
Strange how?

60
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:57,760
My heart raced
whenever he came close.

61
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:04,440
When he smiled at me, I felt happy.

62
00:04:06,330 --> 00:04:08,920
But when he didn't,
when he went cold,

63
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:11,000
my heart just sank.

64
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,480
I wanted to see him every day.

65
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:18,720
And when I did,
I panicked and wanted to run.

66
00:04:20,570 --> 00:04:22,560
But I didn't want him
to disappear either.

67
00:04:24,450 --> 00:04:25,710
Thought I was losing my mind.

68
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:32,000
From what I've heard, I think...

69
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:36,340
you already know how you feel.

70
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:41,840
Hey, let me ask you something.

71
00:04:43,820 --> 00:04:46,680
Honest answer. Do you like him?

72
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,080
Look.

73
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:53,400
A man liking another man
isn't wrong,

74
00:04:54,070 --> 00:04:55,680
nor is it something
to be ashamed of.

75
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:59,040
Centuries ago,
perhaps it was frowned upon,

76
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,480
shaped by the beliefs of their time.

77
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:07,280
But in any era, it was never wrong.

78
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,440
Save.

79
00:05:13,350 --> 00:05:16,320
Answer yourself honestly.
Do you like him?

80
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,360
Yes.

81
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,040
I like Guy.

82
00:05:30,140 --> 00:05:31,550
Good.

83
00:05:31,770 --> 00:05:34,970
If you're clear about
your feelings, don't deny them.

84
00:05:35,450 --> 00:05:36,450
Don't hold back.

85
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:40,160
You're young. You've got time
to figure yourself out.

86
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,840
Whatever you feel,
follow your heart.

87
00:06:07,860 --> 00:06:09,560
But I already messed up.

88
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:11,440
How?

89
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:15,360
Well, now he thinks

90
00:06:15,570 --> 00:06:17,360
I was using him for Grandpa's novel.

91
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,680
He doesn't trust me anymore.

92
00:06:21,260 --> 00:06:23,280
Then you have to earn it back.

93
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:25,860
Make it clear.

94
00:06:26,980 --> 00:06:31,740
Prove to him that
what you feel is real.

95
00:06:34,690 --> 00:06:35,690
Go for it.

96
00:06:36,260 --> 00:06:40,080
If he has feelings for you,
it won't be that hard.

97
00:06:44,430 --> 00:06:46,760
By the way, I've been wondering.

98
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:50,880
Since Grandpa started
writing a BL novel,

99
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:55,440
has he...become more open
to those relationships?

100
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:59,840
I think so, yeah.

101
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:04,760
But it's still not easy
for someone of his generation.

102
00:07:10,690 --> 00:07:12,870
Uncle Sun.

103
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:15,440
I'm sure Grandpa misses you.

104
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:18,200
That's just you.

105
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,000
No, I mean it.

106
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:25,040
If you can find time,
come home for dinner.

107
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:49,480
- Hi.
- You're back.

108
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:51,400
Still up, Grandpa?

109
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:52,640
Mm-hmm.

110
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:54,840
You got back later than usual.

111
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,980
I got worried.
Came down to wait for you.

112
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:15,080
- Grandpa.
- Hmm?

113
00:08:18,030 --> 00:08:20,680
- Can I ask you something?
- Go ahead.

114
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,040
If I actually like a guy,

115
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,200
are you okay with that?

116
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,160
Why are you asking me that?

117
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:30,440
It's just...

118
00:08:31,590 --> 00:08:32,590
I think...

119
00:08:34,010 --> 00:08:35,120
I like Guy.

120
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,640
Don't play with me.

121
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,000
Because all this time,
you've always liked girls.

122
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:43,520
Can't things change?

123
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:47,720
Save, ask yourself first.

124
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,680
Are you simply confused?

125
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:53,040
Maybe it's just a passing feeling.

126
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:55,280
I thought so, at first.

127
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:58,200
But I'm sure now.

128
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:10,040
It's me who roped you into all this.

129
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,280
- So now you're...
- Do you still think...

130
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:16,280
a man liking another man is wrong?

131
00:09:17,540 --> 00:09:23,080
Well, it's...not wrong.
But...it's not normal.

132
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:26,200
Not normal how?
Seems pretty normal to me.

133
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:29,480
I just want you to think it through.

134
00:09:31,650 --> 00:09:33,640
So you don't regret it later.

135
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:39,160
Not as much as I'd regret
never even trying.

136
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:46,320
Would you be disappointed in me
if I were...

137
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:48,520
I would never be.

138
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:52,320
If anything is weighing
on me right now,

139
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:54,120
it's that I might not

140
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:58,360
be able to save Saeng Karun.

141
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:03,040
So...you don't hate me, do you?

142
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,920
You're my grandson.

143
00:10:11,550 --> 00:10:13,560
How could I ever hate you?

144
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:53,400
You should've said that
to Uncle Sun too.

145
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:58,760
Don't bring Sun into this.
That's a different matter.

146
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:02,280
I went to see him.

147
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:08,000
How's he been lately?

148
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:11,600
He seems fine.

149
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:14,920
He said to tell you
he's thinking of you.

150
00:11:32,020 --> 00:11:36,120
Thanks so much, Phuri.
I'll have my grandson look it over.

151
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:40,800
Of course. I've compiled the details
from every publisher for you.

152
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,480
Please look through it.

153
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:45,400
I would be glad to be
among those you consider.

154
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:46,950
Heh...we'll just see.

155
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:51,560
Oh, and that other thing.
Don't forget, please.

156
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:54,360
Of course, sir. I've got you.

157
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:56,920
We'll consider you
Save's ghost writer.

158
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:59,800
Completely under wraps.
You have my word.

159
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:02,120
Thank you. Much obliged.

160
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:06,840
Well, if there's nothing else,
I should get back to work.

161
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,040
Of course. So long, sir.

162
00:12:35,930 --> 00:12:36,930
Hmm.

163
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:45,200
Hey, anybody?

164
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:50,150
This box on the floor.
I almost tripped over it.

165
00:12:56,110 --> 00:12:58,200
- Surprise.
- Surprise.

166
00:12:58,230 --> 00:13:00,030
- Heh.
- Hehe.

167
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:01,030
What's going on?

168
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:04,800
Dad, this is the money
from selling sweets.

169
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:08,560
We've saved it up
for your debt, Father.

170
00:13:08,820 --> 00:13:11,030
Oh, I can't take it.

171
00:13:11,430 --> 00:13:14,120
You keep it for household expenses.

172
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:18,560
That is also taken care of.

173
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:20,150
This is on top of that.

174
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:25,600
Dad, we want to
save Saeng Karun too.

175
00:13:25,630 --> 00:13:27,080
We're in this together.

176
00:13:27,630 --> 00:13:29,760
You must take it, Father.

177
00:13:30,020 --> 00:13:33,440
All of the kids helped us
with the live streams.

178
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:35,360
So everybody wants to help.

179
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,320
You all must've been
working so hard.

180
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:45,120
Dad, it's nothing. Easy.

181
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:48,920
Scorching fire or raging storm,
we'll get through it.

182
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:50,200
For our home.

183
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:54,000
I'm basically Superman
at this point.

184
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:55,640
Oh, boy...

185
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:59,520
Though I admit, I nearly
crashed and burned along the way.

186
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:05,240
Thank you. Both of you.

187
00:14:05,890 --> 00:14:06,890
Yes, Father.

188
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:09,800
Count it and see how much is there.

189
00:14:09,830 --> 00:14:12,200
Heh...must I count?

190
00:14:12,890 --> 00:14:14,000
Just tell me.

191
00:14:14,030 --> 00:14:17,040
I see our young man of the house
can't handle the thrill.

192
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:21,480
Let me show you then.

193
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:26,360
See, Dad, this stack is 5,000 baht.

194
00:14:26,380 --> 00:14:27,440
5,000 baht.

195
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:29,840
And this one's another 5,000.

196
00:16:34,950 --> 00:16:38,360
"If you're clear about
your feelings, don't deny them."

197
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:40,080
"Don't hold back."

198
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:43,280
"Whatever you feel,
follow your heart."

199
00:16:52,690 --> 00:16:53,690
Hey.

200
00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:55,880
We need to talk.

201
00:17:01,410 --> 00:17:02,680
I admit

202
00:17:03,940 --> 00:17:05,520
when I first came to you,

203
00:17:05,820 --> 00:17:08,080
it was to get material
for the novel.

204
00:17:09,990 --> 00:17:10,990
Well,

205
00:17:12,380 --> 00:17:13,960
the orphanage
was about to be taken.

206
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:18,000
I wanted to help Grandpa
write the novel.

207
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:20,640
It was our only way.

208
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:23,160
But I knew...

209
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:25,760
it wasn't fair to you.

210
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:28,080
And it's no excuse for

211
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:31,280
using you like that.

212
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:32,850
You knew?

213
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:35,450
But when I tried things with you...

214
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:38,840
it felt real, Guy.

215
00:17:40,050 --> 00:17:41,200
How can I be sure

216
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,680
this isn't just another scene
in the novel?

217
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:46,280
Perhaps it will be.

218
00:17:48,070 --> 00:17:49,520
But I still like you.

219
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:55,720
These feelings
I have for you are real.

220
00:17:57,910 --> 00:17:59,680
Just saying it doesn't make it true.

221
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:02,310
I can't bring myself to believe you.

222
00:18:08,810 --> 00:18:09,810
Huh.

223
00:18:13,710 --> 00:18:14,960
Dang it.

224
00:18:17,520 --> 00:18:18,720
Serves you right, Save.

225
00:18:28,420 --> 00:18:30,440
Perhaps it will be.

226
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:32,160
But I still like you.

227
00:18:58,970 --> 00:19:00,240
Hey, Save.

228
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:07,710
- We watched your interview.
- Yeah.

229
00:19:07,790 --> 00:19:09,400
So who is it you've been talking to?

230
00:19:13,870 --> 00:19:14,870
Guys.

231
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:18,320
I want to make up with Guy.

232
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,240
Help me out.

233
00:19:24,620 --> 00:19:25,820
Done. Say no more.

234
00:19:28,330 --> 00:19:29,450
Thanks.

235
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:33,320
I want us to perform a short scene
from classic literature.

236
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:36,200
Form your own groups of five to six.

237
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:39,520
Then send a representative up
to draw your assignment.

238
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:42,820
Let's form your groups.

239
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:47,560
- You and me. Together, okay?
- Come on.

240
00:20:02,170 --> 00:20:03,670
Like this, right?

241
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:04,990
- What?
- Okay, let's...

242
00:20:05,020 --> 00:20:06,120
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

243
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:08,040
You do it.

244
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:11,150
- This scene.
- Wow.

245
00:20:16,730 --> 00:20:17,920
- No idea.
- You don't remember?

246
00:20:17,940 --> 00:20:18,940
Not at all.

247
00:20:18,950 --> 00:20:21,360
Alright, there are two lead roles.

248
00:20:21,550 --> 00:20:24,200
Let's vote on who plays them.

249
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,840
Hands up for Guy
in one of the roles.

250
00:20:27,590 --> 00:20:31,680
- Hey, me?
- Come on, you've got the chops.

251
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:33,720
- Me?
- Yep.

252
00:20:34,110 --> 00:20:35,560
No way. I can't act.

253
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:39,240
Hey, respect democracy.
We all voted.

254
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:44,300
You voted without asking
if I want a role.

255
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:47,680
Too bad, we already picked you.

256
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:51,400
Alright, next. Hands up for Save
to play the other role.

257
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:57,480
Okay, so Guy and Save
are the leads. Done.

258
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:02,200
Did you all plan this?

259
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:05,320
No, man. You two are
the obvious choice.

260
00:21:05,580 --> 00:21:07,720
- Yeah.
- Don't make it a thing.

261
00:21:07,740 --> 00:21:08,740
- Sit down.
- Yeah.

262
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:11,980
So what's the story?

263
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,660
The story of Phra Aphai Mani.

264
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:16,480
The scene where
the hermit teaches Sut Sakorn.

265
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:17,480
- What?
- What?

266
00:21:17,990 --> 00:21:19,440
So who plays who?

267
00:21:32,360 --> 00:21:33,360
Hi, grandpa.

268
00:21:33,820 --> 00:21:34,820
Mm-hmm.

269
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:41,880
What's wrong, stuck again?

270
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:44,320
Yeah. Good timing you're here.

271
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:47,200
You said you'd take me
to see the novel earnings.

272
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:49,760
Right, let's go.

273
00:21:50,090 --> 00:21:53,310
We've the three latest chapters
behind a paywall.

274
00:21:53,330 --> 00:21:54,720
Let's see how much we've made.

275
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:00,280
This...

276
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:02,790
- Whoa.
- What?

277
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:03,960
Look there, grandpa.

278
00:22:03,990 --> 00:22:06,840
The text is tiny.
Just read it out to me.

279
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:10,320
Coin income: over 5,000 baht.

280
00:22:10,350 --> 00:22:11,440
Donations...

281
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,240
Total's 15,000 baht.

282
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:17,040
Fifteen thousand.
How is that possible?

283
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:19,360
And that's just the first month.

284
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:22,920
We can actually
start paying off the debt.

285
00:22:23,060 --> 00:22:25,880
At this rate, absolutely.

286
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,800
You're awesome, Grandpa.

287
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:32,680
Good thing I didn't quit.

288
00:22:32,710 --> 00:22:33,500
Haha.

289
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:35,480
Told you you could do it.

290
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:38,200
- Grandpa.
- Mm-hmm.

291
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:40,440
I need a favor.

292
00:22:41,040 --> 00:22:42,280
Go ahead.

293
00:22:42,640 --> 00:22:44,720
Can you record
a verse chanting for me?

294
00:22:45,280 --> 00:22:48,620
- For the school performance.
- Of course. I'm a master at that.

295
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:51,040
I won an award for it
back in school.

296
00:22:51,330 --> 00:22:53,400
I remember you bragging about it.

297
00:22:55,770 --> 00:22:56,770
Here.

298
00:22:57,910 --> 00:22:58,910
Let me see.

299
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:00,800
This part...

300
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:02,280
Right here.

301
00:23:04,710 --> 00:23:07,240
Starting here.

302
00:23:07,620 --> 00:23:10,160
"Never put your trust in man."

303
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:15,920
Okay, I got that. I'll record it.

304
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:18,760
Make it sound good.
Full marks worthy.

305
00:23:19,130 --> 00:23:21,640
Yeah, trust me.

306
00:23:21,950 --> 00:23:24,340
And here...in exchange.

307
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:28,020
Help me post this.

308
00:23:28,660 --> 00:23:30,000
New chapter.

309
00:23:30,900 --> 00:23:32,960
- Sure thing.
- Mm-hmm.

310
00:23:35,840 --> 00:23:39,280
Hey, is this handwriting
or a treasure map?

311
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:41,400
Getting harder to read
every chapter.

312
00:23:41,690 --> 00:23:45,080
Well, if you can't read,
just ask me.

313
00:23:54,020 --> 00:23:55,200
Hello, sir.

314
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:57,800
Oh, hello, hello.

315
00:23:57,800 --> 00:23:59,200
It's Guy.

316
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:01,250
- Hello, Mother.
- Oh, my...

317
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:06,480
Haven't seen you for so long.
I've missed you.

318
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:08,520
I missed you too.

319
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:11,040
Sorry about the live streams.

320
00:24:11,210 --> 00:24:14,160
Oh, not at all.
Don't worry about it.

321
00:24:14,910 --> 00:24:16,600
Save, Guy's here.

322
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,160
How are things?

323
00:24:35,530 --> 00:24:36,530
Where are those guys?

324
00:24:39,010 --> 00:24:42,160
They're coming.
I tagged them in the group.

325
00:24:50,010 --> 00:24:52,600
"Pheem: Dude, I've got
food poisoning. Can't make it."

326
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:53,800
"Jang: I've got a fever."

327
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:56,680
"Ron: Guy, Save,
start rehearsing without us."

328
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:59,350
"I'm taking my mom to the doctor.
I'll get there if I can."

329
00:25:05,260 --> 00:25:06,560
Did you all set this up?

330
00:25:08,040 --> 00:25:09,620
I just wanted a chance
to be with you.

331
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:15,120
Fine. Rehearse and I'll dash out.

332
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:18,200
Okay.

333
00:25:19,300 --> 00:25:21,360
So...have you eaten?

334
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:36,240
Here, eat first then.

335
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:39,520
You know this is my favorite?

336
00:25:40,350 --> 00:25:41,760
I've been paying attention.

337
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,360
Oh, have you?

338
00:25:43,780 --> 00:25:46,400
Mm-hmm. You even knew what I like.

339
00:25:47,230 --> 00:25:50,040
That was me. You ever did the same?

340
00:25:51,230 --> 00:25:54,030
I did. It's your favorite.
I remember.

341
00:26:03,560 --> 00:26:04,720
Not hungry.

342
00:26:05,560 --> 00:26:06,680
Let's just rehearse.

343
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:09,240
Can we go somewhere else?

344
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:12,400
Why?

345
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:15,440
I don't want to be alone with you.

346
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,320
I'm not gonna do anything.

347
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:21,920
I feel uneasy.

348
00:26:24,460 --> 00:26:25,460
Alright.

349
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,320
Follow me.

350
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:42,240
So in this scene, I get pushed off
a cliff by the hermit.

351
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:45,450
- Who plays the hermit?
- Ron.

352
00:26:45,940 --> 00:26:48,240
So I fall, and you come rescue me.

353
00:26:49,180 --> 00:26:51,320
Do I still have to do
the verse chanting?

354
00:26:51,320 --> 00:26:52,960
Because I'd butcher it.

355
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:54,920
I had Grandpa record it.

356
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:57,160
You just lip-sync to his voice.

357
00:26:58,550 --> 00:26:59,550
Here.

358
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:07,740
Argh.

359
00:27:07,740 --> 00:27:10,720
Help Sut Sakorn...

360
00:27:11,850 --> 00:27:12,850
Ugh.

361
00:27:15,110 --> 00:27:16,110
Heh.

362
00:27:17,920 --> 00:27:22,260
And then, you...
ride a rainbow to save me.

363
00:27:22,690 --> 00:27:23,960
Yours truly.

364
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:30,640
Is it a rainbow or a bird?

365
00:27:30,890 --> 00:27:32,240
I looked it up.

366
00:27:32,840 --> 00:27:35,980
Some people interpret
the hermit's rainbow

367
00:27:36,050 --> 00:27:37,170
as a rainbow hawk.

368
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:39,480
Others say it's just a rainbow.

369
00:27:39,840 --> 00:27:42,440
Couldn't decide,
so I combined them.

370
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:47,000
Ahem.

371
00:27:47,170 --> 00:27:48,170
Then what?

372
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:49,480
And...

373
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:55,880
then he carries him up
to the mountaintop.

374
00:28:01,150 --> 00:28:03,880
Argh.

375
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:05,320
Then you...have to...

376
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:06,680
Don't touch me.

377
00:28:07,020 --> 00:28:08,520
You must pull me up.

378
00:28:08,850 --> 00:28:10,240
I'm a sorcerer, though.

379
00:28:10,240 --> 00:28:13,160
I'll cast a spell so you float,
rise up, and follow me.

380
00:28:34,520 --> 00:28:37,520
Then the hermit
teaches Sut Sakorn.

381
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:40,040
Right where it says
"and he teaches."

382
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:43,120
Then lip-sync to
my grandpa's recording.

383
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:46,440
Memorize it too.
Move your lips properly.

384
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:48,520
Is that all?

385
00:28:49,210 --> 00:28:50,210
Mm-hmm.

386
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:54,080
Pheem got us
a real good story, huh?

387
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:57,320
'And he teaches,
"Never put your trust in man."'

388
00:29:28,110 --> 00:29:29,110
Sir.

389
00:29:29,560 --> 00:29:30,680
May I have a word?

390
00:29:31,220 --> 00:29:32,220
Of course.

391
00:29:37,800 --> 00:29:42,480
I know you're still angry at Save.

392
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:48,000
So I wanted to apologize.
I'm the reason you two fought.

393
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:49,960
It's not your fault at all.

394
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:53,150
Hmm? How is it not my fault?

395
00:29:54,220 --> 00:29:57,460
I was the one
who played right along with him.

396
00:29:57,840 --> 00:30:01,760
I know you and Save were
trying to save this place.

397
00:30:02,880 --> 00:30:05,360
Honestly, I've let go of
most of the anger already.

398
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,560
We've been friends a long time.

399
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:10,360
I can tell he genuinely feels bad.

400
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:13,280
Well, that's something.

401
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:16,480
But please don't tell him yet, sir.

402
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:20,200
I'll make him sweat a little
after what he put me through.

403
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:24,240
Ah! My lips are sealed.
Serves him right.

404
00:30:25,230 --> 00:30:26,230
Thank you.

405
00:30:30,250 --> 00:30:32,640
I'm rooting for your novel,
by the way.

406
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:34,680
Waiting for the next chapter.

407
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:38,120
And if you ever need ideas,
hit me up.

408
00:30:38,370 --> 00:30:39,370
Much appreciated.

409
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:42,520
Oh, and if I do pay off the debt,

410
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:47,360
just know
you had a hand in that too.

411
00:30:48,650 --> 00:30:49,650
Thanks, sir.

412
00:30:54,040 --> 00:30:55,320
- Grandpa.
- Hmm?

413
00:30:56,670 --> 00:30:58,350
Guy still doesn't forgive me.

414
00:31:01,470 --> 00:31:02,960
You put him through a lot.

415
00:31:04,610 --> 00:31:06,600
I know. But...

416
00:31:07,780 --> 00:31:11,610
- What? Are you giving up?
- No.

417
00:31:13,130 --> 00:31:16,240
- It's just...
- Then keep going.

418
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,760
Stay the course,

419
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:25,080
and one day, he'll come around.
I'm sure of it.

420
00:31:25,920 --> 00:31:28,160
- Really?
- Of course.

421
00:31:29,810 --> 00:31:32,120
- Heh.
- Sathu.

422
00:31:32,770 --> 00:31:34,120
Keep at it.

423
00:31:35,940 --> 00:31:36,940
Hmph.

424
00:31:37,910 --> 00:31:38,910
Ding-ding.

425
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:40,680
Heh.

426
00:32:02,780 --> 00:32:04,960
Oops, sorry, Phi Oui.
My hands slipped.

427
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:07,800
A broken thing
can't be a bad omen, right?

428
00:32:08,280 --> 00:32:09,480
Hmm...it's nothing.

429
00:32:10,150 --> 00:32:12,080
Let's pick it up
before someone gets hurt.

430
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:13,200
Right, right.

431
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:29,880
Dad, I'll take the money
to the bank for you.

432
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:32,120
Yeah, thanks.

433
00:32:38,050 --> 00:32:40,600
(A tokay gecko tolls
like an ill omen.)

434
00:32:42,370 --> 00:32:44,160
(A tokay gecko tolls
like an ill omen.)

435
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:45,280
Mm...

436
00:32:47,680 --> 00:32:49,640
(A tokay gecko tolls.)

437
00:33:27,070 --> 00:33:29,260
"Account balance: 180,013"

438
00:33:35,970 --> 00:33:37,960
Don't worry anymore, sir.

439
00:33:38,650 --> 00:33:40,040
We'll save this house after all.

440
00:33:52,720 --> 00:33:54,080
Hey, naked hermit.

441
00:33:58,680 --> 00:34:00,040
Hey, hey. Whatchu doing?

442
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:03,560
Hey, hey. What's this?

443
00:34:04,830 --> 00:34:05,830
Hey.

444
00:34:06,860 --> 00:34:09,640
Oh...argh.

445
00:34:09,660 --> 00:34:13,080
Argh.

446
00:34:13,230 --> 00:34:15,680
Phra Chao Ta (elder sage), help me.

447
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:17,680
Help me...

448
00:34:17,700 --> 00:34:18,560
Arr...

449
00:34:18,580 --> 00:34:20,800
- Wu-hu.
- Here I come.

450
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:22,280
Arr.

451
00:34:22,710 --> 00:34:23,710
Hmph.

452
00:34:33,010 --> 00:34:39,280
'A sudden toll rang out,
distant and hollow,'

453
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:46,960
'Startled, he turned,
and looked around to find.'

454
00:34:47,640 --> 00:34:54,800
'A hermit came, borne
on an arc of a rainbow,'

455
00:34:55,360 --> 00:35:00,960
'And bore him up
toward the mountain height.'

456
00:35:02,520 --> 00:35:08,480
'"Put not your trust in man,"
the hermit said,'

457
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:15,280
'Man's depths are dark,
beyond all measure.'

458
00:35:15,760 --> 00:35:22,400
'Though vines may twist
in tangled turns and wind,'

459
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:29,360
'They are not so serpentine
as the human mind.'

460
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:37,800
'Of those who love,
but two are truly true:'

461
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:46,200
'A father's care,
a mother's love for you.'

462
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:53,080
'One refuge more remains
for you to keep:'

463
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:59,080
'Yourself, your faith,
your hands to see you through.'

464
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:05,680
'Keep friends close by,
and keep your foes at bay.'

465
00:36:06,540 --> 00:36:14,200
'Choose well who stays
beside you, child, I say.'

466
00:36:14,900 --> 00:36:21,960
'True wisdom stands above
all lesser knowledge,'

467
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:29,080
'And keeps you safe
from harm in every place.'

468
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:35,240
'Remember this well,
and go claim the staff.'

469
00:36:36,440 --> 00:36:44,160
'It will serve you well
and guard your path.'

470
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:51,400
'When all was said, made clear
for him to see,'

471
00:36:52,360 --> 00:37:02,720
'Gone was the hermit,
lost to mortal sight.'

472
00:37:24,670 --> 00:37:28,430
- Wu-hu...
- Yay.

473
00:37:28,460 --> 00:37:29,460
Fantastic.

474
00:37:53,430 --> 00:37:54,500
Absolutely incredible.

475
00:38:14,930 --> 00:38:15,930
Ahem.

476
00:38:18,500 --> 00:38:19,720
Missed your cue out there, huh?

477
00:38:20,180 --> 00:38:21,180
What cue?

478
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:24,440
You...held my hand for
a really long time.

479
00:38:26,360 --> 00:38:28,880
Yeah, well. First time in a play.

480
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:30,960
Things get a little off, I guess.

481
00:38:31,260 --> 00:38:32,520
Heh.

482
00:38:32,940 --> 00:38:33,940
Okay.

483
00:38:34,480 --> 00:38:36,760
Quit grinning.
I'm still mad at you.

484
00:38:37,920 --> 00:38:41,280
Go ahead, stay mad.
I'm gonna win you back.

485
00:38:49,420 --> 00:38:53,000
And I...
will not stop until you soften.

486
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:56,160
Like when you said
you'd keep chasing me.

487
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:17,500
So...

488
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:21,000
I've arranged a meeting
with the bank next week.

489
00:39:22,240 --> 00:39:25,560
To sort out the debt
once and for all.

490
00:39:27,370 --> 00:39:29,000
Oh, where are your glasses, Father?

491
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:35,320
Oh, that's why your face
looked strange. No glasses.

492
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:37,560
Too much trouble.
They get in the way.

493
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:39,280
But can you even see?

494
00:39:39,970 --> 00:39:41,240
I'm not blind.

495
00:39:41,830 --> 00:39:44,750
- The bank meeting's all set then.
- Sure.

496
00:39:50,550 --> 00:39:55,360
Ah, teenagers. What can you do?
The hormones are in full chaos.

497
00:40:15,280 --> 00:40:16,320
Hello?

498
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:19,640
Hi, this is
Thepnakhon Hospital calling.

499
00:40:19,670 --> 00:40:22,330
Your nephew has been
in a car accident.

500
00:40:24,540 --> 00:40:25,560
What?

501
00:40:25,580 --> 00:40:28,400
Your nephew has been
in a car accident.

502
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:30,600
He needs emergency surgery
right away.

503
00:40:32,040 --> 00:40:35,080
Uh, hello?
Please hold just a moment.

504
00:40:45,250 --> 00:40:46,480
- Sorn.
- Hmm?

505
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:50,280
Mart, someone just called.
Save has been hit by a car.

506
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:51,400
- What?
- What?

507
00:40:52,590 --> 00:40:55,040
Who? Who's calling, Father?

508
00:40:56,130 --> 00:40:57,760
Hello? Hello?

509
00:40:59,930 --> 00:41:01,000
They hung up.

510
00:41:01,690 --> 00:41:03,240
Let me call Save.

511
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:17,600
He's not picking up.

512
00:41:18,520 --> 00:41:20,000
Stay calm.

513
00:41:20,140 --> 00:41:22,960
Could this be
one of those scam calls?

514
00:41:23,200 --> 00:41:25,480
You know, that's a good point.

515
00:41:25,780 --> 00:41:29,400
If Save actually got hit,
wouldn't he call me?

516
00:41:29,420 --> 00:41:30,420
Hmm.

517
00:41:31,650 --> 00:41:34,000
Here. Check it out.

518
00:41:34,030 --> 00:41:35,030
Okay, Dad.

519
00:41:35,450 --> 00:41:38,080
Save showed me an app
to check scam callers.

520
00:41:38,080 --> 00:41:39,800
He installed it for Mart.

521
00:41:40,310 --> 00:41:41,310
Enter this number.

522
00:41:42,720 --> 00:41:43,720
Okay.

523
00:41:45,760 --> 00:41:48,000
It's not flagged as a scam call.

524
00:41:50,180 --> 00:41:52,780
Keep trying Save's number
until someone picks up.

525
00:41:52,820 --> 00:41:53,820
Okay.

526
00:42:02,080 --> 00:42:03,560
- Or maybe...
- Got it?

527
00:42:04,280 --> 00:42:05,280
Not yet.

528
00:42:22,230 --> 00:42:23,230
Hello?

529
00:42:23,270 --> 00:42:26,320
Hello, this is the hospital calling.

530
00:42:26,500 --> 00:42:30,400
Your nephew needs to be taken
into surgery immediately.

531
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:33,280
Tell me first. What's his name?

532
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:35,840
Grandpa, it's me, Save.
Help me, Grandpa. Ow.

533
00:42:35,840 --> 00:42:36,840
Save.

534
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:40,360
- Grandpa, it's me, Save. Help.
- Save.

535
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:44,600
Sir, you must transfer
the surgery fees to us now.

536
00:42:44,600 --> 00:42:47,600
If you don't, your nephew
won't be taken into surgery.

537
00:42:48,140 --> 00:42:49,560
How much do you need?

538
00:42:49,660 --> 00:42:52,320
The surgery fee is 180,000 baht.

539
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:54,200
Operating room: 50,000 baht.

540
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:56,240
Anesthesia: 20,000 baht.

541
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:58,640
Other medical costs: 50,000 baht.

542
00:42:58,640 --> 00:43:00,560
Total: 300,000 baht.

543
00:43:01,080 --> 00:43:03,800
Oh-ho. I don't have that much.

544
00:43:04,120 --> 00:43:06,440
Then the surgery fee first.

545
00:43:06,440 --> 00:43:08,960
So the doctor can operate in time.

546
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:13,080
Hold on...just a moment.
Stay on the line.

547
00:43:26,480 --> 00:43:30,520
- Grandpa, it's me, Save. Help.
- Save.

548
00:43:30,770 --> 00:43:32,730
- Ow, Grandpa.
- Save.

549
00:43:33,210 --> 00:43:35,920
- Help me, Grandpa.
- He has lost consciousness.

550
00:43:37,440 --> 00:43:38,800
"Fund transferred: 180,000"
I sent it.

551
00:43:39,200 --> 00:43:40,920
Which hospital is he at?

552
00:43:42,250 --> 00:43:46,380
We're sorry. The number cannot
be reached at this time.

553
00:43:47,200 --> 00:43:48,200
Hello?

554
00:43:48,960 --> 00:43:50,040
Hello?

555
00:43:50,040 --> 00:43:51,800
Grandpa, Mom said
we got a scam call?

556
00:44:11,280 --> 00:44:12,280
Grandpa.

557
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:18,040
Grandpa.

558
00:44:21,960 --> 00:44:25,400
No wonder. The gecko was chirping
since morning.

559
00:44:25,540 --> 00:44:27,920
Yeah, that really was a bad omen.

560
00:44:29,720 --> 00:44:31,010
It's because of you, Save.

561
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:33,440
You put that banking app
on his phone.

562
00:44:33,680 --> 00:44:35,080
Dad, quiet down.

563
00:44:35,850 --> 00:44:37,160
Grandpa's already stressed enough.

564
00:44:39,170 --> 00:44:41,600
So what do we do now?

565
00:44:42,210 --> 00:44:44,360
Where should we report this first?

566
00:44:45,030 --> 00:44:46,030
Uh.

567
00:44:47,890 --> 00:44:49,500
Contact the bank first.

568
00:44:50,290 --> 00:44:53,400
Freeze his account,
then file a police report.

569
00:45:05,790 --> 00:45:07,770
"Balance: 13 baht."

570
00:45:13,200 --> 00:45:15,350
Went to the police
just to get lectured.

571
00:45:16,350 --> 00:45:19,230
I know scammers are
all over the news.

572
00:45:19,230 --> 00:45:20,980
But we all make mistakes, don't we?

573
00:45:21,280 --> 00:45:25,480
Exactly. Who would've known
AI can fake voices now?

574
00:45:26,080 --> 00:45:30,480
From now on,
just hang up on unknown callers.

575
00:45:30,480 --> 00:45:32,240
Don't even answer.

576
00:45:32,640 --> 00:45:36,880
If it sounds real,
check with someone else first.

577
00:45:37,480 --> 00:45:40,240
Don't click on any suspicious links.
Okay, Dad?

578
00:45:40,800 --> 00:45:44,800
If they want personal information,
never give it out.

579
00:45:45,070 --> 00:45:47,560
And never transfer money to anyone.

580
00:45:47,880 --> 00:45:48,880
Understood, Dad?

581
00:45:54,790 --> 00:45:55,910
It's alright, Grandpa.

582
00:45:56,960 --> 00:45:58,480
Anyone can make mistakes.

583
00:45:59,320 --> 00:46:00,800
I owe you all an apology too.

584
00:46:02,900 --> 00:46:05,720
I lost the money
you worked so hard for.

585
00:46:11,210 --> 00:46:14,520
It's fine, Father.
Money can be earned back.

586
00:46:18,560 --> 00:46:21,880
It's okay, Grandpa.
Don't be so hard on yourself.

587
00:46:29,210 --> 00:46:35,160
'"Put not your trust in man,"
the hermit said,'

588
00:46:35,680 --> 00:46:40,560
'Man's depths are dark,
beyond all measure.'

589
00:46:43,160 --> 00:46:46,440
His voice was nice,
so I set it as my ringtone.

590
00:46:55,950 --> 00:46:56,950
Grandpa.

591
00:46:58,940 --> 00:47:00,600
Don't overthink it, Grandpa.

592
00:47:02,560 --> 00:47:06,440
You did it quickly because
you were so worried about me.

593
00:47:08,440 --> 00:47:11,440
I am...touched by that.

594
00:47:14,790 --> 00:47:18,680
Next month, there'll be
new money coming in anyway.

595
00:48:23,400 --> 00:48:24,640
You silly old fool.

596
00:48:31,930 --> 00:48:36,960
Everyone, keep a close eye
on Grandpa, okay?

597
00:48:37,150 --> 00:48:38,290
Okay, Phi Sorn.

598
00:48:38,750 --> 00:48:41,770
I'm worried about him too.
He must be crushed.

599
00:48:41,790 --> 00:48:42,660
Mm-hmm.

600
00:48:42,690 --> 00:48:44,320
He just put that money together.

601
00:48:44,940 --> 00:48:46,480
And it vanished just like that.

602
00:48:49,330 --> 00:48:51,040
These scammers are truly rotten.

603
00:48:51,780 --> 00:48:53,280
When will they get rid of them?

604
00:48:59,540 --> 00:49:02,160
Okay, Phi Mart. Keep me posted.

605
00:49:02,480 --> 00:49:05,120
Mm-hmm.
Are you dropping by tomorrow?

606
00:49:05,610 --> 00:49:09,720
If I show up, it'll only
make him feel worse.

607
00:49:11,800 --> 00:49:13,000
Please look after him.

608
00:49:13,830 --> 00:49:15,160
Will do.

609
00:49:24,990 --> 00:49:27,470
"Mom: Missed calls."

610
00:50:49,970 --> 00:50:50,970
Oh?

611
00:50:58,900 --> 00:51:00,080
Sleeping in Grandpa's room?

612
00:51:00,920 --> 00:51:04,560
Mm-hmm. We couldn't leave him
alone tonight.

613
00:51:07,920 --> 00:51:08,920
Oh, Snow.

614
00:51:15,470 --> 00:51:19,480
I want to stay with Grandpa.
He needs some comforting.

615
00:51:31,980 --> 00:51:34,480
Dad, we're coming in.

616
00:52:52,960 --> 00:52:53,960
Sleep tight, Dad.

617
00:52:57,020 --> 00:52:59,600
Save, get some sleep.

618
00:53:03,040 --> 00:53:04,040
Come on, go to sleep.

619
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:41,680
Where'd you get it from?

620
00:53:41,960 --> 00:53:42,960
My boyfriend.

621
00:53:42,990 --> 00:53:43,990
Boyfriend?

622
00:53:44,020 --> 00:53:45,890
You can't go very far
with grades like that.

623
00:53:46,080 --> 00:53:47,920
I got bad grades just like you.

624
00:53:48,200 --> 00:53:49,240
Snow.

625
00:53:49,240 --> 00:53:50,240
You know, Dad?

626
00:53:50,760 --> 00:53:53,830
I never wanted to stay here
because of you.

627
00:53:54,120 --> 00:53:55,910
If the patient refuses surgery,

628
00:53:55,910 --> 00:53:58,520
there's a real chance of
permanent blindness.

629
00:54:00,240 --> 00:54:06,080
The world keeps
turning every day.

630
00:54:06,080 --> 00:54:11,320
And we keep
turning in its play.

631
00:54:11,320 --> 00:54:14,800
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

632
00:54:14,800 --> 00:54:17,320
We just might see
the world within.

633
00:54:17,320 --> 00:54:21,440
Let's walk together,
day by day.

634
00:54:21,440 --> 00:54:26,440
Come take the step,
what do you say?

635
00:54:32,960 --> 00:54:36,520
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

636
00:54:36,520 --> 00:54:40,440
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

637
00:54:40,440 --> 00:54:45,560
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

638
00:54:45,560 --> 00:54:48,040
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

639
00:54:48,040 --> 00:54:50,760
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

640
00:54:50,760 --> 00:54:55,640
And land where
our hearts both grow.

641
00:54:56,000 --> 00:55:01,880
The world keeps
turning every day.

642
00:55:01,880 --> 00:55:07,200
And we keep
turning in its play.

643
00:55:07,200 --> 00:55:10,440
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

644
00:55:10,440 --> 00:55:13,160
We just might see
the world within.

645
00:55:13,160 --> 00:55:17,320
Let's walk together,
day by day.

646
00:55:17,320 --> 00:55:22,200
Come take the step,
what do you say?

